19/09/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The chairman of the BiH Defence Reform Commission, James Locher, said Friday (17 September) that the country has fulfilled 11 out of 14 preconditions for entry into NATO's Partnership for Peace Programe.
Speaking after a session of the commission, Locher said a system of budgeting defence resources management would be established, as well as a state-level operational centre for military and intelligence affairs.
He also said BiH is committed to meeting the final condition for entry into the programme:
full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal.
(Nezavisne novine - 18/09/04;
Fena - 17/09/04)
